### Bug #6: Phantom Third Speaker
**Problem**: Deepgram occasionally assigns a third speaker ID (Speaker_2, Speaker_3, etc.)
due to background noise, mic bleed, or diarization errors. There are only ever TWO
people in this interview: Flavio (Speaker_1) and Claude Assistant (Speaker_0). Any
utterance tagged Speaker_2 or higher is a misattribution.

**Fix**: Claude Assistant should ignore any speaker tag above Speaker_1. If a card
arrives tagged Speaker_2 or higher, treat it as belonging to whichever speaker
was last active. On the frontend, these orphaned cards should be visually flagged
so Flavio can quickly select them and reassign to Speaker_0 or Speaker_1 with
one tap.

